    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Feature already in Vim?\n\nNo\n\n### Feature description\n\nWhen using `:terminal` I would like (on Windows) to start a powershell terminal with the parameter `-NoLogo`, but apparently there is no way to achieve it.\r\n\r\n\r\nAccording to the documentation (https://neovim.io/doc/user/various.html#:terminal)\r\n\r\n````\r\n:te[rminal][!] [{cmd}]\tRun {cmd} in a non-interactive 'shell' in a new |terminal-emulator| buffer. Without {cmd}, start an interactive 'shell'.\r\n````\r\n\r\nThus if providing a parameter, the shell is non-interactive.\r\n\r\nAlso something like  `set shell=powershell.exe -nologo` does not help, as \"powershell.exe -nologo\" is not a valid shell.\r\nAnd `set shellcmdflag` does not help, as it is used only for non-interactive shells too.\r\n\r\nOther shells, like \"bash\" also accepts parameters, so this problem is not windows or powershell specific.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
